---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const release = {
  tag: "release-2026-03-11",
  archiveUrl:
    "https://github.com/tldev/openinterstate/releases/download/release-2026-03-11/openinterstate-release-2026-03-11.tar.gz",
  manifestUrl:
    "https://github.com/tldev/openinterstate/releases/download/release-2026-03-11/manifest.json",
  checksumsUrl:
    "https://github.com/tldev/openinterstate/releases/download/release-2026-03-11/checksums.txt",
  githubReleaseUrl: "https://github.com/tldev/openinterstate/releases/tag/release-2026-03-11"
};
---

<BaseLayout title="Releases | OpenInterstate">
  <section class="page-intro">
    <p class="kicker">Releases</p>
    <h1>Dated, documented, and checksummed.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Public releases are the primary product surface. The first public release is now available
      and is backed by a manifest, checksums, and explicit dataset counts.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="card-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <p class="kicker">Latest</p>
        <h3>{release.tag}</h3>
        <p>563 corridors, 68,881 corridor exits, 101,522 places, and 250 reference routes filtered to strict interstate naming.</p>
        <div class="actions">
          <a class="button button-primary" href={release.archiveUrl}>Download release archive</a>
          <a class="button button-secondary" href={release.githubReleaseUrl}>GitHub release</a>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <p class="kicker">Formats</p>
        <h3>CSV + GPX + GeoJSON</h3>
        <p>The v1 release favors immediate usability and a stable public release path over stricter packaging.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <p class="kicker">Contract</p>
        <h3>Manifest + schema version</h3>
        <p>The release manifest defines the machine-readable release surface.</p>
        <p><a href={release.manifestUrl}>manifest.json</a> · <a href={release.checksumsUrl}>checksums.txt</a></p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
